ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I think a more apt title for this course would be "non-research aspects of research." That is, you will learn how to typeset papers, craft presentations, post research online, etc. My feeling is that most first year graduate students have this knowledge already, but I would certainly recommend the course to a graduate student without these skills.
The ethical issues discussed in this course is very important and interesting.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Helped understand how issues of priority should be resolved in math research
It neither deepened my knowledge of mathematics nor contributed to my research, but I do not think it was a waste of time.
